idden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529942\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mjb1665702748492.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mjb1665702748492.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mjb1665702748492.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mjb1665702748492\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the installation script to update or upgrade an older version of the RMS License Manager and the Cloud Plug-in, or to switch license type from a cloud-served license to a license file or license code (or vice versa).\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__li_d30452e1_d30453e1_d30454e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__p_d67679e1_d67680e1_d67681e1\">Run the installation script.\n The script notices that you already have an RMS License Manager installed.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__li_d30455e1_d30456e1_d30457e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__p_d67682e1_d67683e1_d67684e1\">When prompted, choose what you want to do with\n               this installation: </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__li_d30458e1_d30459e1_d30460e1\">Update this installation.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__li_d30461e1_d30462e1_d30463e1\">Return the license and uninstall this\n                     installation—for details, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"luh1665702748423.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luh1665702748423.html\" title=\"To uninstall the RMS License Manager, use the uninstall script that was created in the directory you specified during installation. You will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine.\">Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix</a>. If you are\n                     using a license file, this option will only uninstall the installation. <p class=\"p\">The\n                        installer now detects if you have a cloud-served license or license file in\n                        place.</p></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__li_d30464e1_d30465e1_d30466e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__p_d67688e1_d67689e1_d67690e1\">Choose whether you want to continue using the\n               existing license or configuration file. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__li_d30467e1_d30468e1_d30469e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">y</code>—use the existing license or configuration file. This is\n                     recommended for an upgrade as no additional license activation will take place. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__li_d30470e1_d30471e1_d30472e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">n</code>—use or generate a new file. Choose this if you are changing\n                     the type of license. <p class=\"p\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__p_d67685e1_d67686e1_d67687e1\">When switching to a\n                        cloud-served license, you are prompted to enter your Entitlement ID and\n                        proxy settings, and the license is activated. When switching to a license\n                        file, you are prompted to first return your cloud-served license and\n                        uninstall the RMS License Manager.</p> The script now stops the old RMS\n                     License Manager and Cloud Plug-in and then copies the new files.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mjb1665702748492__li_d30473e1_d30474e1_d30475e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">When prompted, choose whether you want to start the service. Select yes\n                  (<code class=\"ph codeph\">y</code>) to start the RMS License Manager and Cloud Plug-in, or no\n                  (<code class=\"ph codeph\">n</code>) to do so later. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qhf1665702748352.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qhf1665702748352.html\" title=\"To start or stop the RMS License Manager, use the following commands.\">Starting and Stopping the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a>. </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529942\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529942\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux Use the installation script to update or upgrade an older version of the RMS License Manager and the Cloud Plug-in, or to switch license type from a cloud-served license to a license file or license code (or vice versa). Run the installation script. The script notices that you already have an RMS License Manager installed. When prompted, choose what you want to do with this installation: Update this installation. Return the license and uninstall this installation—for details, see Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix . If you are using a license file, this option will only uninstall the installation. The installer now detects if you have a cloud-served license or license file in place. Choose whether you want to continue using the existing license or configuration file. y —use the existing license or configuration file. This is recommended for an upgrade as no additional license activation will take place. n —use or generate a new file. Choose this if you are changing the type of license. When switching to a cloud-served license, you are prompted to enter your Entitlement ID and proxy settings, and the license is activated. When switching to a license file, you are prompted to first return your cloud-served license and uninstall the RMS License Manager. The script now stops the old RMS License Manager and Cloud Plug-in and then copies the new files. When prompted, choose whether you want to start the service. Select yes ( y ) to start the RMS License Manager and Cloud Plug-in, or no ( n ) to do so later. For more information, see Starting and Stopping the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}